occurrenceRemarks: Vaccinium erythrocarpum? I can confidently identify it in bloom, but I have never seen it (or tried to identify it) when in fruit. I think this is right though, based on the description in my field guide to the trees and shrubs of the Southern Appalachians. Particularly telling: leaves minutely toothed and ciliate, hairy along veins; twigs dark red or brownish red to green, older bark either close or peeling; fruit solitary, in axils of leaves, dark red (they look almost black on the pictures, but when the sunlight hit them they were dark red)
